    "chemicalDescription": [
      "s-Haematococcus Lacustris Oligopeptide-1 is a single chain peptide consisting of alanine, aspartic acid, glutamic acid, glycine, leucine, lysine, proline, tryptophan and valine. It is synthetically produced based on a sequence from Acetamidase found in Haematococcus lacustris. The parent protein contains a maximum of 146 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation, and consists of the proper sequence from the 20 standard amino acids."
    ],
